-- Turkish Stocks: Koza Anadolu, Tupras Are Active in Istanbul
-- B y   B e n j a m i n   H a r v e y
-- 2012-07-10T15:31:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-10/turkish-stocks-koza-anadolu-tupras-are-active-in-istanbul.html
Turkey’s benchmark  ISE National 100
Index (XU100)  climbed 0.8 percent to 63,123.95 at the close in Istanbul,
its highest close since April 3.  The following shares were active. Stock symbols are in
parentheses.  Koza Anadolu Metal Madencilik Isletmeleri AS (KOZAA)  , a
Turkish miner, rose 3.5 percent to 3.89 liras. The company was
placed on the recommended stocks list of Ekspres Invest, the
brokerage unit of Denizbank AS, which said new projects offer
high growth potential. The 12-month price estimate was 5.12
liras, Ekspres said in an e-mailed report to clients today.  Tupras Turkiye Petrol Rafinerileri AS (TUPRS TI), the
country’s biggest refiner of crude oil, advanced as much as 1.6
percent before closing up 0.3 percent at 38.70 liras. The
company’s price estimate was raised to 49 liras from 46.8 liras
at Goldman Sachs Group Inc. The  average 12-month estimate  among
28 analysts is 45.1 liras, according to data compiled by
Bloomberg.  To contact the reporter on this story:
